Hypopygium (
Figs. 22–24
). Anal tergite bands Y­type. Anal point (length 50–59 m , width 8–9 m ) narrow and parallel side. Laterosternite IX with 1–2 setae. Transverse sternapodeme 36–45 m long. Gonocoxite (length 68–126 m ) with 3–4 setae. Superior volsella symmetrical pad­like (length 32–50 m , width 32–50 m ) with 10–14 short setae. Inferior volsella rounded apically (length 63–68 m , width 27–32 m ). Gonostylus (length 117–171 m , width 27–36 m ) slightly curved, widest at about distal 1 / 3 . HR 0.54–0.74 .
